The paper discusses the design of big data systems with a focus on traceability and reusability of data or process elements. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB) and cybersecurity (cs.CR) sub-categories, as these are areas where traceability and data management are important. The paper also mentions the use of meta-data and description-driven design, which are techniques commonly used in cyberinfrastructure (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the design philosophy in health informatics and business process management, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
